# Audio-Tampering-Detection-and-localization-
In today’s digital world, audio recordings are widely used in communication, media, journalism, legal investigations, and cybersecurity. Modern editing software allows users to manipulate audio easily by cutting, splicing, adding noise, or compressing files. Because of this, fake or modified audio can spread misinformation and reduce trust in digital evidence.
This project presents an Artificial Intelligence (AI)-based system that can automatically detect whether an audio file has been tampered with and also identify the exact manipulated regions.
